                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout>The ogham inscription is located on the right face of the slab and includes a wavy stem-line. The front face contains the lower section of a <rs type="decoration">crucifiction scene</rs>, portraying Christ from the waist down, dressed in a tunic, and two figures on each side (Richardson 1928, 226). Below the crucifix is a panel that may have contained an <rs type="decoration" cert="low">interlaced design</rs>, but the stone is so badly worn that the pattern has almost faded (ibid). The back face may have also been decorated but is no longer discernible (ibid).</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
