                        <provenance type="found">The first illustration of the ogham is by John Borland from <date>2009</date> as part of the Records of the Royal Commission on the Ancient and Historical Monuments of Scotland (RCAHMS) collection published online on Canmore <ref target="https://canmore.org.uk/site/33412/monifieth"/>. The stone was found re-used at the foot of the kirkyard wall in <date>1928</date> and given to the National Museum of Scotland (Richardson 1928, 226).
